abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio said the city would not meet its year-end deadline to complete a program involving thousands of homes damaged by Hurricane Sandy.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio said the city would not meet its year-end deadline to complete a program involving thousands of homes damaged by Hurricane Sandy.
lead_paragraph: The program created to help homeowners in New York recover from Hurricane Sandy will not meet its year-end deadline, officials said this week, the latest setback for the yearslong effort to rebuild thousands of homes in the city that were damaged in the storm.

abstract: Social figures, fashion magnates, models, actors and rafts of the largely unsung turned out in all their finery on Monday to honor Bill Cunningham.
snippet: Social figures, fashion magnates, models, actors and rafts of the largely unsung turned out in all their finery on Monday to honor Bill Cunningham.
lead_paragraph: Among the luminaries assembled at Carnegie Hall on Monday to memorialize Bill Cunningham, who died on June 25 at age 87, was former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg. Stepping briskly to the stage, Mr. Bloomberg reminded the gathering of more than 1,000 that few people knew better than Mr. Cunningham himself “that the best runways are the streets of New York.”

headline_main: Mosul, Obama, U.S. Presidential Race: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: In March, a hacked email shows, Mrs. Clinton was presented with a “first cut” list of vice-presidential prospects by her campaign chairman.
snippet: In March, a hacked email shows, Mrs. Clinton was presented with a “first cut” list of vice-presidential prospects by her campaign chairman.
lead_paragraph: Hillary Clinton could have shared the Democratic presidential ticket with Bill Gates — or with his wife, Melinda. She could have named Michael R. Bloomberg, the billionaire former New York mayor, as her running mate. Or she could have chosen to reward a loyal friend and fund-raiser by making Gov. Terry McAuliffe of Virginia her No. 2.
